modules.description: The module provides direct access to a comprehensive set of UTF-8 encoded Unicode emojis, enabling retrieval of individual emoji characters and sequences with support for skin tone modifiers, gender variations, and composite glyphs (e.g., couples, handshakes). It operates on string-based representations of emojis, organized into categories like facial expressions, animals, objects, and gestures, with explicit handling of diversity in human figures and symbolic icons. This facilitates use cases such as text rendering in applications, UI development requiring inclusive emoji representation, and processing emoji-rich content in OCaml programs.
